"```sql\nSELECT a.account_id\nFROM account a\nJOIN disp d ON a.account_id = d.account_id\nJOIN client c ON d.client_id = c.client_id\nJOIN district dist ON c.district_id = dist.district_id\nWHERE c.gender = 'F'\nORDER BY c.birth_date ASC, dist.A11 ASC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the account number of the oldest female client with the lowest average salary. It joins the necessary tables using the foreign key relationships and filters for female clients. The results are ordered by birth date (oldest first) and average salary (lowest first), and the query returns only the top result."